Class FirstOrderCollectionImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyc.kb.client.KbObjectImpl

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.cyc.kb.FirstOrderCollection, com.cyc.kb.KbCollection, com.cyc.kb.KbObject, com.cyc.kb.KbTerm

    public class FirstOrderCollectionImpl
extends KbCollectionImpl
implements com.cyc.kb.FirstOrderCollection
    A FirstOrderCollection object is a facade for a #$FirstOrderCollection in Cyc KB. A #$FirstOrderCollection is a specialization of #$Collection. It is a collection of collections that have only #$Individual as its instances. The higher level APIs that use the KB API utilize this subclass (specialization) of KBCollection (#$Collection.) So we have a class to support strongly typing such collections.

      • findOrCreate

        public static FirstOrderCollectionImpl findOrCreate(String nameOrId)
                                             throws com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException,
                                                    com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        Find or create a FirstOrderCollection object named nameOrId. If no object exists in the KB with the name nameOrId, one will be created, and it will be asserted to be an instance of #$FirstOrderCollection. If there is already an object in the KB called nameOrId, and it is already a #$FirstOrderCollection, it will be returned. If it is not already a #$FirstOrderCollection, but can be made into one by addition of assertions to the KB, such assertions will be made, and the object will be returned. If the object in the KB cannot be turned into a #$FirstOrderCollection by adding assertions (i.e. some existing assertion prevents it from being a #$FirstOrderCollection), a KBTypeConflictExceptionwill be thrown.
        Parameters:
        nameOrId - the string representation or the HLID of the #$FirstOrderCollection
        Returns:
        a new FirstOrderCollection
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException

      • findOrCreate

        public static FirstOrderCollectionImpl findOrCreate(String nameOrId,
                                    com.cyc.kb.KbCollection constraintCol)
                                             throws com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException,
                                                    com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        Find or create a FirstOrderCollection object named nameOrId, and also make it an instance of constraintCol in the default context specified by KBAPIDefaultContext#forAssertion(). If no object exists in the KB with the name nameOrId, one will be created, and it will be asserted to be an instance of both #$FirstOrderCollection and constraintCol. If there is already an object in the KB called nameOrId, and it is already both a #$FirstOrderCollection and a constraintCol, it will be returned. If it is not already both a #$FirstOrderCollection and a constraintCol, but can be made so by addition of assertions to the KB, such assertions will be made, and the object will be returned. If the object in the KB cannot be turned into both a #$FirstOrderCollection and a constraintCol by adding assertions, a KBTypeConflictExceptionwill be thrown.
        Parameters:
        nameOrId - the string representation or the HLID of the #$FirstOrderCollection
        constraintCol - the collection that this #$FirstOrderCollection will instantiate
        Returns:
        a new FirstOrderCollection
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
